<html>
    <head><title>more on select element int html forms</title></head>
<body>
Use the<b>size</b>  attribute to specify the number of visible values:
<br><form>
    Choose your car:
<select name="cars" size="3" multiple>
  <option value="volvo">Volvo</option>
  <option value="saab">Saab</option>
  <option value="fiat">Fiat</option>
  <option value="audi">Audi</option>
</select>
<input type="submit" value="submit"></form>
<br>Use the <b>multiple</b> attribute to allow the user to select more than one value:
</body>
